content:
@WG-prioritization/alerts issue #93753 has been requested for prioritization.

Procedure

  • Priority?
  • Regression?
  • Notify people/groups?
  • Needs I-nominated?
For the record, this is a PR, not an issue. (Triagebot is a bit imprecise in its wording here.)
feel like the underlying bug here is P-high, cause we accidentally stabilized an attribute

There does not seem to be much precedent of prioritizing PRs, and no precedent of prioritizing PRs with a regression label

PRs with regression labels: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pulls?q=is%3Apr+label%3Aregression-from-stable-to-nightly%2Cregression-from-stable-to-beta%2Cregression-from-stable-to-stable

PRs with priorities: https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pulls?q=is%3Apr+label%3AP-critical%2CP-high%2CP-medium%2CP-low

Overlap: none

Maybe rustbot shouldnâ€™t even automatically add the I-prioritize on PRs with regression labels?

I can't think of a single case where a PR needs to be prioritized so I'll remove the label.
Good to know about this PR being beta-nominated, though. It will be on the table at the next t-compiler meeting.

PRs with priorities [...]

these look like arbitrary use of that label (I can imagine something like: "this is something important for push forward"), so I would remove the P-* label to avoid confusion
